parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Overheating due to Faulty Cooling Fan
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, transmission, and other components, leading to costly repairs, breakdowns, and potentially even fires. This can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: temperature gauge in the red zone
and smoke or fire from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or may deploy unexpectedly, causing harm to occupants.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard illuminates
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the passenger airbag deploys without warning
the driver's side airbag deploys without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Rotational Rate Sensor (Yaw) Causing Uncommanded Brake Application and Loss of Vehicle Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty yaw sensor can cause the Dynamic Stability Control (DSC) system to malfunction, leading to uncommanded brake application, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle pulls violently to one side
the ABS engages and causes the vehicle to judder.
